{"lemma":"ذَرْقُ","slug":"ذَرْقُ","root":"ذ.ر.ق","root_slug":"ذ-ر-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-ر-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13831","n13833","n13834"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B0%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%82%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dung, to mute, to excrete"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ذَرَقَ (ḏaraqa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dung, dropping, guano"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bird's-foot trefoil (Lotus corniculatus)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"blue melilot (Melilotus caerulea) or furrowed melilot (Melilotus sulcata) or elegant sweetclover (Melilotus elegans)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sicklefruit fenugreek, sickle-shaped fenugreek (Trigonella corniculata syn. T. balansae, elatior, esculenta)","examples":[{"text":"حندقوقي بري: هو الذرق والحباقي أيضاً. ديسقوريدوس في الرابعة: لوطوس أغريوس ومعناه الحندقوقي البري وهو ينبت كثيراً بالبلاد التي يقال لها ليبوى وله ساق طولها نحو من ذراعين أو أكثر، ويتشعب منها شعب كثيرة ولها ورق شبيه بورق الحندقوقي الذي ينبت في المروج، ويقال له طريفلان، وله بزر شبيه ببزر الحلبة إلا أنه أصغر منه بكثير وهو كريه الطعم.","english":"Wild trefoil: It is the ḏuraq and also the ḥabāqīy. Dioskorides IV, 110: lōtós ágrios, meaning wild trefoil, grows copiously in Libya. It has a stalk of a length of two branches or more, and it branches off much. And it has leaves similar to trefoil growing on meadows. It has seeds similar to that of fenugreek, but much yellower and of a disagreeable taste."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13831","headword_ar":"ذَرَقَ","root":"*rq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aroqN","text_ar":"ذَرْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) said of a bird, (S, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It muted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dunged;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, Mgh, Msb;) [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaraqa","text_ar":"زَرَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*rAq","text_ar":"اذراق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Zj, JK, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*oraAqN","text_ar":"اـِذْرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (JK:) it is also, sometimes, (assumed tropical:)  said of a man: (S, * TA:) and the latter is sometimes (tropical:)  said of a beast of prey, and [particularly] of a fox. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mataY ta*oruwqN","text_ar":"مَتَى تَذْرُوقٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"عَلَى النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When wilt thou behave in a lightwitted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foolish, manner towards men?"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"utter foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obscene, language against them?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA kalaAmN ya*oraqu Ealayohi","text_ar":"هٰذَا كَلَامٌ يَذْرَقُ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"language, that is deemed foul."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^a*oruqan~aka A_ino lamo turab~iEo","text_ar":"لَاَذْرُقَنَّكَ اـِنْ لَمْ تُرَبِّعْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a phrase meaning a threat. (TA. [But how it should be rendered, unless it be said by a woman to her husband, (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~aEa liA@moraA^atihi","text_ar":"رَبَّعَ لِا@مْرَاَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA*rqn~k","text_ar":"لاذرقنّك"},{"kind":"text","text":"be for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^a*oruqan~a Ealayoka","text_ar":"لَاَذْرُقَنَّ عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", I know not.])       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ariqa AlmaAlu","text_ar":"ذَرِقَ المَالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in the JK written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*araqa","text_ar":"ذَرَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but said in the TA to be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariH","text_ar":"فَرِح"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cattle suffered from eating the herb called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uraq","text_ar":"ذُرَق"},{"kind":"text","text":", is] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~uraqu","text_ar":"الذُّرَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","Zj","JK"]},{"entry_id":"n13833","headword_ar":"ذَرْقٌ","root":"*rq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dung"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, Mgh) of a bird; (S, Mgh;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uraAqN","text_ar":"ذُرَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AZ, TA:) [or] of the bustard ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubaAraY","text_ar":"حُبَارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":") and the like: (JK:) the former word an inf. n. used as a subst. in this sense. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","Mgh","AZ","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n13834","headword_ar":"ذُرَقٌ","root":"*rq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain plant, resembling"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fisofisap","text_ar":"فِسْفِسَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain herb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HanodaquwqN","text_ar":"حَنْدَقُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herb lotus, melilot, sweet trefoil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bird's-foot-trefoil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the present day]: (JK, IDrd, S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it has a slight and sweet odour, and grows in"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plains such as are called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiyEaAn","text_ar":"قِيعَان"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in places where water collects and stagnates; and sheep, or goats, suffer from eating it, and sometimes become distended in their bellies:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, TA:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AHn, JK, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","JK","IDrd","S","K","AHn"]}]}}